originalText.text:
Staff are extremely rude and very very poor communication when I visited around 4:30PM on Dec 20.

I understood they were busy and patiently waited in line in my car for 10+ minutes before they said anything to me. When they finally acknowledge my existence, before I was able to say anything, the first thing they said was asking me to turn around and leave as if I was making their life miserable. Both staff told me to "just go". I told them I have been waiting for 10min+ and one guy finally said turn around and wait, then they will take my car. I did, except they let in 5 other cars in the next few minutes, continuing to ignore my existence. That's when I decided to leave.

Most of the parking garage staff in Manhattan are nice and sometimes heart warming. The staff at this place are the worst that I've ever seen. I don't know what made them to be like this, but I wouldn't recommend this place until that's changed.

originalText.text: Gustavo (or so he claims his name is) is EXTREMELY rude, racist, islamophobic, and unprofessional. He served every customer before me every single time I came (five times in a span of 6 months) and would bring in all the new cars before he acknowledged me. He won’t provide me his boss’s information to file a formal complaint and threatened me when I asked for it. I highly recommend going to ANY OTHER garage in the neighborhood. The garage on 60th and Lex are much more professional and friendly and WAY cheaper when you book online.
